-- Ex-divs to take 6.5 points off FTSE 100 on April 30
-- By Tricia Wright
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 06:21AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 28 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.

According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take 6.53 points off the index. COMPANY (RIC) DIVIDEND   DIVIDEND ESTIMATEDTYPE   (pence)  IMPACT  Admiral Group   <ADML.L>   Combined   50.60.3934   Fresnillo   <FRES.L>   Special 6.8 cents  0.0271  G4S <GFS.L>Final   5.54   0.3409  ITV <ITV.L>Combined6.40.9503  Reed Elsevier   <REL.L>Final  17.95   0.8321  Travis Perkins  <TPK.L>Final  21  0.2056  Tesco   <TSCO.L>   Final  10.13   3.2282  Weir Group  <WEIR.L>   Final  33.20.2798  William Hill<WMH.L>Final   7.90.2703  Among FTSE 250 <.FTMC> companies going ex-dividend are:COMPANY  (RIC)   DIVIDEND